In 2022/23 there were 13.4 million antipsychotic items prescribed, a 1.30% increase from 2021/22. This increase was driven by a 1.58% increase in BNF paragraph antipsychotic drugs. Both other paragraphs in this section decreased from 2021/22 to 2022/23. Antipsychotic depot injections decreased by 3.79% and drugs used for mania and hypomania decreased by 0.68%

#### Figure 14: Number of identified patients by financial year - BNF 4.2: Drugs used in psychoses and related disorders

```{r annual_patients_0402, out.width="100%"}

