Source: [Annual statistical summary tables - Drugs used in psychoses and related disorders](https://nhsbsa-opendata.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/mumh/mumh_bnf0402_2022_23.xlsx)

An estimated 850,000 identified patients were prescribed at least one antipsychotic item in 2022/23. This was 0.99% more than 2021/22. Identified patients have increased over time since 2015/16 to 2022/23, and show a similar upward trend to items.

Any patient who was prescribed items from more than one BNF paragraph is counted in the subtotal for each relevant paragraph. However, these patients have only been counted once in the BNF section totals for each relevant section. The total number of identified patients is therefore lower than if the totals for each paragraph are added together.

