There were an estimated 251,000 identified patients prescribed antipsychotic items in 2022/23 in the most deprived areas in England. This was more than twice as many as the 124,200 patients that were prescribed antipsychotic items in the least deprived areas. In general, more people were prescribed antipsychotics in more deprived areas in 2022/23. This pattern has remained consistent since 2015/16.

